-- ON THE MOVE-Wells Fargo hires three advisers from Morgan Stanley
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Tue Mar 18, 2014 01:38PM EDT
-- None



March 18 (Reuters) - Wells Fargo Advisors <WFC.N> said on Tuesday it hired three financial advisers from Morgan Stanley <MS.N>, where combined they managed almost $500 million in assets.

Gary Parese, Mark Phillips and Tom Nolan joined Wells Fargo's Westport, Connecticut office this month reporting to market manager, Chris Calabrese. Parese managed about $270 million in assets at Morgan Stanley, while Phillips managed about $120 million and Nolan roughly $100 million. Their combined industry experience totals more than 80 years and their annual fees and commissions was in excess of $3.1 million.